



# Creating Practice Questions

>* This prompt helps people study with practice questions

## Overview
This prompt produces a quiz/ practice questions 	for people who are studying for a test, or people who just want to know more about certain topics. 

It solves the problem of people not knowing how to study, it allows them to study with practice questions about the current topic they are learning.

**Best For :**
- Studying for a school test
- Learning new concepts
- Studying for work

**Output**
-
- A typical output looks like the practice Questions with answers that go along with what you are studying and what level you are at with it and what you are specifically learning  
- ## Quick Start
### 1. Copy the prompt
I am a student studying [class/what you're studying for]. The class is for [grade/ skill level you want to learn] and right now we are learning about[subject you want to learn more about]. I am a [stage you're at with the concept] in this field. Provide [how many practice questions you want] practice questions for the subject I am currently working on based on my grade and skill level. Some examples of questions I want to be included are [at least 2 questions you want]. I want it to be formatted with [ multiple choice, writing prompts, etc]
### 2. Fill in placeholders
Replace these with your specific information:
- `[class/what you're studying for]` - you will put the name of the class you want practice question for, or what you are interested in learning.
- `[grade/skill lever you want to learn]` - you will put what your grade number is, or how far along you are with learning the skill
- `[Subject you want ot learn more about]` - you will put the certain things you are learning about in the class, or the specific things you want to know/learn
- [Stage you are at with the concept] - you will put how much you know, if you are a beginner, intermediate, or anything else.
- [how many practice questions you want] - you will put the number of questions you want in the practice test
- [at least two questions for the subject] - two questions you want on the test that are relevant to the subject
- [multiple choice, writing prompts, etc]  -you will put how you want it to be formatted

